  "text": "An unusual triallelic pattern was also detected within analysed accessions -at the locus ISV2 in the cultivar Irsai Oliver (Figure 2 ), representing Type 2 of triallelic pattern [CITATION_1] . Such somatic mutation and its accumulation were designated as a way of diversification process and phylogeny [CITATION_2] and as a slow but constant evolution ongoing in grapevine [CITATION_3] . Generally, mutations are important genetic events in grapevine, generating variation (phenotypes) in important traits such as berry colour and flavour, date of ripening, size and compactness of bunches, yield, and others. ",
